rec\ntors to Jay E. Adams, May 22, 1908,\ndeed to lot 11. block 7, neb. 2906. East\nEnglewood; $5O.\nYale Hicks to R L Eschenberg. F.\nG. Hillje and W R Kink. May 12\n1908. deed to 700 acres of Jouqtiin\nLeal grant, division 1, volume 211,\npages 505-508: $5OOO.\nJ. N. Campbell et al. to Edward Epp\nJune 11. 1908, deed to south one-third\noZ lots 2 and 3, neb. 2598. on South\nHores street; $175.\nD K. Furnish, trustee of Kiinney Co.\nto Thomas N. Smith of Bexar county\nJune 16, 1908. deed to lots 24 to 30.\nblock 6. cb. 1782. Beacon Hill; $lO. etc.\nugust Pascal et al., of Iberia\nParish, La., to Gustav Etter of Bexar\ncounty, June 16, 1908, deed to lot 7.\nblock 3. neb. 744, on west side of\nSouth Alamo street: $2500.\nJohn A. and Anna Hof to Eliza\nbeth P. Docker. May 26. 1908. deed\nto southeast part of lot 6. and south\nwest part of lots 4 and 2. block 4, neb.\n445, on corner of Avenue E and Sev\nenth streets; $7700.\nE. G. and Lizzie Baker, of South\nPoland county, Maine, to E. A. Fox.\nof Bexar county. May 26. 1908, deed\nto lots 1 to 9, block 1. neb. 2194 Don\naldson's addition; $l.\nRiverside Land and Improvement\ncompany by B. L. Naylor to M. L. Ar\nnold. March 5, 1908, deed to lot 8,\nblock 7, Riverside Park addition;\n$7OO.\nj. Vandandingham and A. McCaw\nley, to R. Papie. June 8. 1908, deed\nto lot 23. neb. 2924. ocl. 112. range 4,\ndivision 1. oh Nevada street; $l.\nW. C. Sullivan to Max B. Mayer,\nJune 1. 1908, dc< d to lot 18. block 31,\nneb. 544 on Nolan and Walnut streets;\nj $5OOO.\n1 To Keep Baby\u2019s Milk Warm.\nCover a hot water bag with one of\nouting flannel in which there has\nJ been made a pocket about the size of\nj a baby\u2019s bottle. When going to bed\nfill the bottle as usual, and place It\nir the pocket. Then fill the water bag\nwith hot water and put it at thji.bot\ntom of the baby\u2019s crib, coveri\u00dfK it\nwith a blanket When the baby wakes\nfcr Its bottle in the night the milk\nwill be ready in an instant \u2014The Juno\nDelineator.\nTHU CSV AL FLAT\nProspective Tenant\u2014There Is hardly\nroom In this room for a bedstead.\nJanitor\u2014l know, you'll have to palnJ\nyour furniture on the wall.\nHis Strategy Made\nTaft the Leader\nWho managed the campaign of Secre-\ntary Taft, which ueenis about to be\ncrowned with success. Hitchcock\nRATTLE OF THE PINS.\nWhite Rose vs. Dullnig's Selections\nat Sommers' garden, and K club vs.\nSocials at Muth's garden are tonight\u2019s\ngames.\nThe Turner members will have\ntheir regular Wednesday evening\npractice tonight on their alleys.\nThe Bexar Bowling club will hoid\ntheir mid-weckly practice tonight ou\nthe Beethoven alleys.\nThe Mission garden alleys will be\noccupied by the Royal Achates in\ntheir regular weekly practice tonight.\nBeware of\nAny Physic That Brings Pain\nGriping and pain will never occur un\nless there is irritation.\nSalts and harsh pills bring their results\nby irritation\u2014by causing the bowel\nfluids to flow.\nBo pepper in the eyes or nostrils will\ncause fluids to flow. But is it wise\nto treat a delicate membrane thus?\nDo so for a time and the membrane\nwill harden. That is how Nature\nAwards off such attacks. The you\nneed larger doses.\nEventually the calloused bowels fail in\ntheir functions entirely. Then you\nhave chronic constipation.\nNo wise person will ever abuse the\nbowels in that way. They will use\nCasearets.\nCascarets nezer cause pain. That\nproves that their action is natural.\nYet they are just as effective as harsh\nphysic.\nTHE STATE BANK TRUST CO.\n321 EAST HOUSTON ST. SAN ANTONIO, TEXAS\nWill Handle All Your Business\nPromptly and Cheerfully.\nW. T. PrMldMt. J. H. HAn a\nFRANK H. HITCHCOCK\nwent at his task in a thoroughly busk\nness-like manner, at times he was so\nsecretive that the newspaper men\ndubbed him \u2018\u2018Old Sleuth.\"\nWestern Schoolgirl\u2019s Greeting.\nAt the last congressional reception\nthe president had at least one bright\nspot to color the monotony. Many\nschoolgirls were among the invited,\nand as the delegation from one school\ncame up. blushing and with shaking\nknees, a western maiden, healthy and\nblooming, with the air of the prairies\nstill about her. was presented.\n\"I'm delighted to meet you, Miss\nR \u2014\u2014said the president, giving her\nhis patent \"pass along\" handshake.\nFor one brief gurglingly blissful in-\nstant the western girl beamed with\njoy. and then from the fulness of her\nheart gushed forth. \u201cSame here.\"\nIf the bowels are calloused, you may\nneed a Cascaret twice a day at the\nstart. But you soon cease to need\nthem at all.\nThose who know the Injury done by\nharsh physics never use anything\nbut Cascarets.\nCascarets cure the trouble. Cathartics\nonly make it worse.\nCascarets are candy tablets. They are sold\nby all druggists, but never In bulk. Be sure Ks\nget the genuine, with CCC on every tablet.\nThe box la marked Uka this:\nThe vest-pocket box Is 10 cents.\nThs month-tresttaent box SO cents.\n12.000.000 botes io;d annually gig","height":"26644","width":"20452"}}
